title: After Sweep, 'Dogs Up to No. 5 in USCHO Poll
text:
After Sweep, 'Dogs Up to No. 5 in USCHO Poll 
By Zach Schneider After Sweep, 'Dogs Up to No. 5 in USCHO Poll October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 1:11 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team moved up two spots to No.5 in the United States College Hockey Online (USCHO) Division I poll, which was released on Monday morning. 
The Bulldogs received a single first-place vote in the poll and are coming off a two-game sweep of in-state rival Minnesota, beating the Gophers 3-1 and 3-0 in a home-and-home series. 
UMD is one of six National Collegiate Hockey Conference (NCHC) teams to crack the nation's top 15 this week. 
For full results of this week's USCHO Division I men's poll, click here. 
UMD is next in action Oct. 23-24 on the road against Notre Dame.
